On 7/9/07, Greg Potts <greg(-at-)pottsfamily.ca> wrote:
>
> Hi Ned,
> Use a voltmeter to measure voltage at the battery and at the coil before
> you start the engine. If there is a significant voltage drop, check the
> voltage at the terminals on the ignition switch next. This will tell you
> where the voltage drop is occurring... it's in the wire from
> battery-ignition switch, the switch itself, or the wire from switch-coil.
> Once you have that sorted out you should be OK.
